, let's start with the entrypoint file, `app.py`.\n\napp.py\n```python\nfrom flask import Flask, render_template, request, redirect, url_for\nfrom flask_sqlalchemy import SQLAlchemy\nfrom forms import PoemForm, CommentForm\n\napp = Flask(__name__)\napp.config['SQLALCHEMY_DATABASE_URI'] = 'sqlite:////tmp/test.db'\ndb = SQLAlchemy(app)\n\nfrom models import Poem, Comment\n\n@app.route('/')\ndef index():\n    poems = Poem.query.order_by(Poem.date_posted.desc()).all()\n    return render_template('index.html', poems=poems)\n\n@app.route('/poem/<int:poem_id>', methods=['GET', 'POST'])\ndef poem(poem_id):\n    poem = Poem.query.get(poem_id)\n    form = CommentForm()\n\n    if form.validate_on_submit():\n        comment = Comment(text=form.text.data, poem_id=poem_id)\n        db.session.add(comment)\n        db.session.commit()\n        return redirect(url_for('poem', poem_id=poem_id))\n\n    comments = Comment.query.filter_by(poem_id=poem_id).all()\n    return render_template('poem.html', poem=poem, comments=comments, form=form)\n\n@app.route('/upload', methods=['GET', 'POST'])\ndef upload():\n    form = PoemForm()\n\n    if form.validate_on_submit():\n        poem = Poem(title=form.title.data, text=form.text.data, author=form.author.data)\n        db.session.add(poem)\n        db.session.commit()\n        return redirect(url_for('index'))\n\n    return render_template('upload.html', form=form)\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    db.create_all()\n    app.run(debug=True)\n```\n\nNext, let's create the `models.py` file.\n\nmodels.py\n```python\nfrom app import db\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nclass Poem(db.Model):\n    id = db.Column(db.Integer, primary_key=True)\n    title = db.Column(db.String(100), nullable=False)\n    text = db.Column(db.Text, nullable=False)\n    author = db.Column(db.String(50), nullable=False)\n    date_posted = db.Column(db.DateTime, default=datetime.utcnow)\n\nclass Comment(db.Model):\n    id = db.Column(db.Integer, primary_key=True)\n    text = db.Column(db.Text, nullable=False)\n    poem_id = db.Column(db.Integer, db.ForeignKey('poem.id'), nullable=False)\n    date_posted = db.Column(db.DateTime, default=datetime.utcnow)\n```\n\nNext, let's create the `forms.py` file.\n\nforms.py\n```python\nfrom flask_wtf import FlaskForm\nfrom wtforms import StringField, TextAreaField, SubmitField\nfrom wtforms.validators import DataRequired\n\nclass PoemForm(FlaskForm):\n    title = StringField('Title', validators=[DataRequired()])\n    text = TextAreaField('Text', validators=[DataRequired()])\n    author = StringField('Author', validators=[DataRequired()])\n    submit = SubmitField('Upload')\n\nclass CommentForm(FlaskForm):\n    text = TextAreaField('Comment', validators=[DataRequired()])\n    submit = SubmitField('Post')\n```\n\nFinally, we need to create the HTML templates. We'll need `index.html`, `poem.html`, and `upload.html`. I'll provide a basic structure for these files, but you'll need to fill in the details based on your specific design requirements.\n\nindex.html\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n    <title>Poem Website</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <h1>Welcome to the Poem Website</h1>\n    <!-- Loop through the poems and display them -->\n    {% for poem in poems %}\n        <h2>{{ poem.title }}</h2>\n        <p>{{ poem.text[:100] }}...</p>\n        <a href=\"{{ url_for('poem', poem_id=poem.id) }}\">Read More</a>\n    {% endfor %}\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\npoem.html\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n    <title>{{ poem.title }}</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <h1>{{ poem.title }}</h1>\n    <p>{{ poem.text }}</p>\n    <p>By {{ poem.author }} on {{ poem.date_posted }}</p>\n\n    <!-- Display the comment form -->\n    <form method=\"POST\">\n        {{ form.hidden_tag() }}\n        {{ form.text.label }}<br>\n        {{ form.text(size=32) }}<br>\n        {{ form.submit() }}\n    </form>\n\n    <!-- Loop through the comments and display them -->\n    {% for comment in comments %}\n        <p>{{ comment.text }}</p>\n        <p>Posted on {{ comment.date_posted }}</p>\n    {% endfor %}\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\nupload.html\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n    <title>Upload a Poem</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <h1>Upload a Poem</h1>\n\n    <!-- Display the upload form -->\n    <form method=\"POST\">\n        {{ form.hidden_tag() }}\n        {{ form.title.label }}<br>\n        {{ form.title(size=32) }}<br>\n        {{ form.text.label }}<br>\n        {{ form.text() }}<br>\n        {{ form.author.label }}<br>\n        {{ form.author(size=32) }}<br>\n        {{ form.submit() }}\n    </form>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\nThis is a basic implementation of the website. There are many ways to expand and improve this, such as adding user authentication, improving the design, adding more features, etc. But this should give you a good starting point."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "a) Install dependencies:\n\n```bash\npython3 -m venv venv\nsource venv/bin/activate\npip install flask flask_sqlalchemy flask_wtf\n```\n\nb) Run all necessary parts of the codebase:\n\n```bash\nexport FLASK_APP=app.py\nflask run\n```"}]